FBIS4-48454 "drafr097_c_94006" FBIS-AFR-94-097 Daily Report 18 May 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA 7,000 MK Members Train for Integration Into SANDF 7,000 MK Members Train for Integration Into SANDF MB1805201294 Johannesburg SAPA in English 1853 GMT 18 May 94 MB1805201294 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Text] Pretoria May 18 SAPA -- Almost 7,000 former Umkhonto we Sizwe (MK) [Spear of the Nation; ANC military wing] troops are being processed into the SA [South African] National Defence Force [SANDF] at Wallmansthal outside Pretoria, SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] radio news reported on Wednesday. A spokesman at the base said the group would be trained by MK until the end of next month. If they passed a selection process after their initial training they would be allowed to choose a career in one of the four arms of the SANDF.
